<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="180" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,1829]" box="[199,1332,1732,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1732,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Etymology</emphasis>
. “ 
<taxonomicName box="[350,463,1732,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata" status="sp. n.">Cingulata</taxonomicName>
” means “banded”, after the conspicuous spinulose band of the corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,327,1829]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,438,1767,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
. The small size and the broad, not concave forewing costa is an unusual combination of characters within this lineage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
